This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image reconstruction and correction. The use of deep learning also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves matrix computations and optimization, which could place it in the mathematical modeling (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the use of neural networks for interpolation could place it in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves signal processing and information theory, which could place it in the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
